	(332, 3, 'Pat beef dry and sprinkle with spices on all sides, pressing to adhere. Heat oil in a large flameproof roasting pan set across 2 burners over high heat until just smoking, then brown beef on all sides, about 2 minutes."'),
	(332, 4, 'Roast in middle of oven until an instant-read thermometer inserted diagonally 2 inches into center registers 120°F, about 25 minutes. Let beef stand in pan 25 minutes. Beef will continue to cook as it stands, reaching 130°F (medium-rare)."'),
	(332, 5, 'Whisk together oil, lemon juice, shallot, and salt in a bowl, then add pepper to taste."'),
