	(2292, 1, 'In a kettle of boiling salted water cook the fennel for 15 minutes, or until it is barely tender. Transfer the fennel to a cutting board, let it cool, and cut it lengthwise into 1/3-inch-thick slices. In a large skillet heat the oil and the butter over mo'),
	(2305, 1, 'Combine vinegar, orange juice concentrate, parsley, lemon peel and orange peel in small bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. (Dressing can be prepared up to 8 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Rewhisk dressing before using.)"'),
