	(7483, 1, 'Bring sugar, ginger, and 1/3 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat; let steep for 10 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a medium pitcher (you should have 1/2 cup); discard ginger. Cover and c'),
	(7483, 2, 'Fill four 6-ounce glasses with ice cubes. Add carrot juice and lime juice to ginger syrup in pitcher; stir well. Divide elixir among prepared glasses.\r'),
	(7490, 1, 'Stir all ingredients in bowl to blend. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Chill at least 2 hours and up to 1 day.\r'),
	(7490, 2, 'Pour 1 cup warm water into large bowl; sprinkle yeast over. Let stand until mixture is foamy, about 10 minutes. Mix in 1/4 cup oil and salt. Combine both flours in medium bowl. Stir enough flour mixture into yeast mixture 1/2 cup at a time to form slightl'),
	(7490, 3, 'Meanwhile, heat 2 tablespoons oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add lamb mixture; sauté until just cooked through, about 3 minutes. Transfer to plate."'),
	(7490, 4, 'Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.\r'),
	(7490, 5, 'Punch dough down. Divide into 4 equal pieces. Cover; let stand 10 minutes. Preheat oven to 450°F. Roll out each dough piece on floured surface to 7-inch square. Top each with 1/4 of charmoula, then 1/4 of lamb, pressing to adhere to dough. Oil 2 large bak'),
	(7490, 6, 'Bake breads until cooked through and brown on bottom, about 15 minutes. Serve warm."'),
	(7496, 1, 'Toss arugula with olive oil, lemon juice, and peel. Toss to coat."'),
	(7505, 1, 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Brush 2 large baking sheets with oil. Toss potatoes with 2 tablespoons oil in large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Spread potatoes on sheets in single layer. Roast until almost tender, about 30 minutes."'),
