	(17786, 1, 'Blend vinegar and shallots in blender or processor. With machine running, gradually add oil. Season with salt and pepper."'),
	(17786, 2, 'Combine romaine, radicchio and endive in large bowl. Toss with enough vinaigrette to coat."'),
	(17793, 1, 'Roast and peel bell peppers. Finely chop onion.\r'),
	(17793, 2, 'In a food processor or blender purée roasted peppers until smooth. In a large heavy saucepan cook onion in butter over moderately low heat, stirring, until soft, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook, stirring, 2 minutes. Stir in grits and add 2 cups milk '),
	(17793, 3, 'Stir in roasted-pepper purée, Tabasco, and salt and pepper to taste. Grits may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered, in a buttered 11-inch gratin or other shallow baking dish (about 6-cup). Reheat grits in a 400° F. oven until hot, about 15 minutes."'),
	(17801, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Butter 9 1/4x5 1/4x3-inch loaf pan. Line bottom and 2 long sides with waxed paper. Whisk flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, salt, and baking soda in medium bowl to blend. Using electric mixer, beat butter in large bowl until f'),
	(17801, 2, 'Bake bread until tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 1 hour 10 minutes. Cool bread in pan on rack 15 minutes. Cut around bread at short ends to loosen from pan. Turn bread out onto rack; peel off waxed paper. Cool bread completely. (Can be '),
